<font color="#FF0000">JUST ABOUT THEM!</font><br>
<tt>Tue May 27  0:11:47 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
They died because they were asked to perform a service for their country. As I said, no matter what your political thoughts or persuasion, this alters not the fact that these folks gave the ultimate for their country. I believe not one wanted to make this sacrifice, which makes it all the more sad and humbling. As I also said, there are 364 other days to argue politics, to argue if they died for naught or otherwise. On this day, the talk of &quot;politics&quot; should not be diminish their memory. With that said, I know you enough, Mike, to know that this is not your intent. We each must do, in our own way, what we can to remember our fallen comrades, those of our parents, and our parents parents. My best to you, Mike, on this day. I, also, had you in my thoughts these past few days.
<p><code>-- docdel@maui.net  (Doc Del) </code><p>


